
You want a website that looks like a presentation (slides) to explain your IoT Ambulance Project — not just a working app but something you can show in class/project demo.

Here’s a simple HTML + CSS + JavaScript website that acts like a presentation slideshow:

<!DOCTYPE html> <html lang="en"> <head> <meta charset="UTF-8"> <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"> <title>IoT Ambulance Project</title> <style> body { margin: 0; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background: #111; color: white; text-align: center; } .slide { display: none; padding: 50px; height: 100vh; box-sizing: border-box; } .active { display: block; } h1, h2 { color: #00bfff; } button { background: #00bfff; color: white; border: none; padding: 10px 20px; margin: 10px; border-radius: 5px; cursor: pointer; } button:hover { background: #008ecc; } .nav { position: fixed; bottom: 20px; width: 100%; text-align: center; } </style> </head> <body> <!-- Slide 1 --> <div class="slide active"> <h1>🚑 IoT Ambulance Project</h1> <h2>Finding Nearby Hospitals</h2> <p>Using IoT and GPS technology to save lives by quickly locating the nearest hospitals in emergencies.</p> </div> <!-- Slide 2 --> <div class="slide"> <h2>📌 Problem Statement</h2> <p>During emergencies, ambulances lose precious time searching for available and nearby hospitals.</p> <p>Manual searching leads to delays, risking patients' lives.</p> </div> <!-- Slide 3 --> <div class="slide"> <h2>⚙️ IoT-Based Solution</h2> <ul style="text-align:left; max-width:600px; margin:auto;"> <li>Ambulance equipped with IoT devices & GPS tracker</li> <li>Real-time location shared with a web system</li> <li>System searches nearest hospitals automatically</li> <li>Navigation link provided to ambulance driver</li> </ul> </div> <!-- Slide 4 --> <div class="slide"> <h2>💡 Features</h2> <ul style="text-align:left; max-width:600px; margin:auto;"> <li>Real-time ambulance tracking</li> <li>Automatic nearest hospital detection</li> <li>Navigation using Google Maps</li> <li>Can integrate hospital availability in future</li> </ul> </div> <!-- Slide 5 --> <div class="slide"> <h2>🎯 Benefits</h2> <p>✅ Saves time in emergencies</p> <p>✅ Reduces manual searching effort</p> <p>✅ Faster response improves survival chances</p> </div> <!-- Slide 6 --> <div class="slide"> <h2>🚑 Demo (Prototype)</h2> <button onclick="findHospitals()">Search Nearby Hospitals</button> <p id="location"></p> <div id="hospital-list"></div> </div> <!-- Slide 7 --> <div class="slide"> <h2>✅ Conclusion</h2> <p>IoT Ambulance System provides a smart, efficient, and life-saving solution by connecting ambulances with nearby hospitals in real-time.</p> </div> <!-- Navigation --> <div class="nav"> <button onclick="prevSlide()">⬅ Prev</button> <button onclick="nextSlide()">Next ➡</button> </div> <script> let currentSlide = 0; const slides = document.querySelectorAll(".slide"); function showSlide(index) { slides.forEach((s, i) => s.classList.toggle("active", i === index)); } function nextSlide() { currentSlide = (currentSlide + 1) % slides.length; showSlide(currentSlide); } function prevSlide() { currentSlide = (currentSlide - 1 + slides.length) % slides.length; showSlide(currentSlide); } // Demo Hospital Finder function findHospitals() { if (!navigator.geolocation) { alert("Geolocation not supported"); return; } navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition((pos) => { const lat = pos.coords.latitude.toFixed(3); const lon = pos.coords.longitude.toFixed(3); document.getElementById("location").innerText = `Current Location: ${lat}, ${lon}`; const hospitals = [ { name: "City Care Hospital", distance: "2.3 km" }, { name: "Metro Health Center", distance: "3.8 km" }, { name: "LifeLine Emergency", distance: "5.1 km" } ]; const list = document.getElementById("hospital-list"); list.innerHTML = ""; hospitals.forEach(h => { list.innerHTML += `<p><b>${h.name}</b> - ${h.distance} away</p>`; }); 

Each slide explains one part of your project (Problem, Solution, Features, Benefits, Demo, Conclusion). Buttons Next ➡ / ⬅ Prev let you move like a PowerPoint presentation. Includes a Demo slide where the ambulance can find nearby hospitals (dummy data). 

Would you like me to also make this presentation look modern with animations and background images (like a professional pitch deck), or keep it simple and minimal for class use?

